<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="581" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1612,2033]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="581" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1612,1637]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" box="[485,641,1612,1637]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" refString="Anker, A. (2011) Six new species and three new records of infaunal alpheid shrimps from the genera Leptalpheus Williams, 1965 and Fenneralpheus Felder &amp; Manning, 1986 (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zootaxa, 3041, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2011">
Anker (
<number box="[574,634,1613,1637]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[656,921,1613,1637]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[656,921,1613,1637]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">Leptalpheus mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[982,1133,1613,1637]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[982,1133,1613,1637]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar, the later being distinguished from the former mainly by the presence of a small crest on the carapace above each eye, and the shape of the lateral lobe of the uropodal protopod. Although of small size, these crests are very conspicuous in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,299,1720,1744]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[151,299,1720,1744]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly in lateral view (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" box="[674,811,1720,1745]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" refString="Anker, A. (2011) Six new species and three new records of infaunal alpheid shrimps from the genera Leptalpheus Williams, 1965 and Fenneralpheus Felder &amp; Manning, 1986 (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zootaxa, 3041, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2011">
Anker 
<number box="[752,811,1721,1745]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 
<number box="[875,903,1720,1745]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="15.0">15</number>
A, B). A topotypical specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1287,1436,1721,1744]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1287,1436,1721,1744]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited in the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 
<collectingCountry box="[883,959,1757,1780]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">France</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[978,1066,1757,1781]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">MNHN</collectionCode>
Na 
<number box="[1111,1183,1756,1781]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="13624.0">13624</number>
), examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" refString="Anker, A. (2011) Six new species and three new records of infaunal alpheid shrimps from the genera Leptalpheus Williams, 1965 and Fenneralpheus Felder &amp; Manning, 1986 (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zootaxa, 3041, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2011">
Anker (
<number box="[159,219,1793,1817]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="2011.0">2011</number>
: 
<number box="[233,262,1793,1817]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="22.0">22</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
apparently did not have these crests. The 
<typeStatus box="[763,861,1792,1817]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">holotype</typeStatus>
(female) and the allotype (male) of 
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1436,1793,1816]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1285,1436,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were originally deposited at the Colección Nacional de Crustáceos (
<collectionCode box="[923,1005,1829,1853]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">CNCR</collectionCode>
), in 
<collectingCountry box="[1055,1140,1828,1853]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">Mexico</collectingCountry>
D.F., but are currently on loan to Darryl L. Felder of the University of Louisiana. On our request, D. L. Felder revised the two 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1865,1889]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">type</typeStatus>
specimens and provided illustrations of the lateral view of the frontal area of the carapace (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1292,1900,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1459,1481]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,535,1446]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1364,531,1446]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Leptalpheus mexicanus Ríos &amp; Carvacho, 1983, female (A – D, EMU- 8784). A, anterior part of carapace and appendages, dorsal view; B, anterior part of carapace, lateral view; C, major cheliped, lateral view; D, right uropod and telson. Leptalpheus mexicanus Ríos &amp; Carvacho, 1983 (E – F, CNCR- 2506); E, female holotype, anterior part of carapace, lateral view; F, male allotype, anterior part of carapace, lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231609/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[1278,1292,1900,1925]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
E, F). These figures show that both 
<typeStatus box="[409,457,1937,1961]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[619,767,1937,1960]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[619,767,1937,1960]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess a very low crest above each eye, a character which was not mentioned nor illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rios" box="[578,858,1972,1997]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" refString="Rios, R. &amp; Carvacho, A. (1983) Caridean shrimps of the Gulf of California III. Leptalpheus mexicanus, new species (Crustacea, Decapoda, Alpheidae). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 3, 306 - 313. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1548265" type="journal article" year="1983">
Ríos &amp; Carvacho (
<number box="[792,850,1973,1997]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in their original description of the species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" refString="Ramos, G. E. (1995) Nuevos registros de camarones alfeidos (Crustacea, Decapoda, Alpheidae) para el Pacifico de Colombia. In: Cantera, J. R. &amp; Restrepo, J. D. (Eds.), Delta del Rio San Juan, Bahias de Malaga y Buenaventura, Pacifico Colombiano. Tomo II. Colciencias. Universidad EAFIT y Universidad del Valle, Colombia, pp. 127 - 153." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Ramos (
<number box="[159,217,2008,2033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName box="[333,481,2009,2032]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[333,481,2009,2032]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[550,663,2008,2033]" name="Colombia" pageId="7" pageNumber="580">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, not illustrating these crests in his material (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos" box="[1203,1348,2008,2033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" refString="Ramos, G. E. (1995) Nuevos registros de camarones alfeidos (Crustacea, Decapoda, Alpheidae) para el Pacifico de Colombia. In: Cantera, J. R. &amp; Restrepo, J. D. (Eds.), Delta del Rio San Juan, Bahias de Malaga y Buenaventura, Pacifico Colombiano. Tomo II. Colciencias. Universidad EAFIT y Universidad del Valle, Colombia, pp. 127 - 153." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Ramos 
<number box="[1288,1348,2008,2033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<number box="[1405,1418,2009,2033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="580" value="1.0">1</number>
); however, his drawings are rather diagrammatic and may not be accurate. Nevertheless, the presence or absence of the carapacial crests above the eyes can no longer be used as a distinctive character between 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1356,189,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1356,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately, the other two 
<typeStatus box="[613,720,224,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[759,908,224,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[759,908,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, deposited at the 
<collectionCode box="[1110,1209,224,248]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/wndr-bidk" name="Centro de Investigacion Cientifica y de Educacion Superior de Ensenada" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">CICESE</collectionCode>
, Ensenada, 
<collectingCountry box="[1343,1431,223,248]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, are no longer available. The other important characters in distinguishing 
<taxonomicName box="[981,1130,261,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[981,1130,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[1201,1350,260,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[1201,1350,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the size and shape of the marginal tooth of the uropodal protopod. The material of 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1192,296,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1192,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Estero de Urías (EMU- 
<number box="[232,289,332,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="8784.0">8784</number>
) features two short teeth separated by a shallow concavity (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1098,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1459,1481]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,535,1446]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1364,531,1446]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Leptalpheus mexicanus Ríos &amp; Carvacho, 1983, female (A – D, EMU- 8784). A, anterior part of carapace and appendages, dorsal view; B, anterior part of carapace, lateral view; C, major cheliped, lateral view; D, right uropod and telson. Leptalpheus mexicanus Ríos &amp; Carvacho, 1983 (E – F, CNCR- 2506); E, female holotype, anterior part of carapace, lateral view; F, male allotype, anterior part of carapace, lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231609/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">
Fig. 
<number box="[1083,1098,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
D), much similar to what is illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" box="[308,460,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" refString="Anker, A. (2011) Six new species and three new records of infaunal alpheid shrimps from the genera Leptalpheus Williams, 1965 and Fenneralpheus Felder &amp; Manning, 1986 (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zootaxa, 3041, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2011">
Anker (
<number box="[395,453,368,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[510,659,368,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[510,659,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, both characters cited hereabove should no longer be considered valid for separating one species from the other.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" box="[199,350,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" refString="Anker, A. (2011) Six new species and three new records of infaunal alpheid shrimps from the genera Leptalpheus Williams, 1965 and Fenneralpheus Felder &amp; Manning, 1986 (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zootaxa, 3041, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2011">
Anker (
<number box="[285,342,440,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned other morphological differences between 
<taxonomicName box="[954,1103,440,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[954,1103,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1308,440,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1159,1308,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a comparison between his single specimen, a male of 
<quantity box="[752,840,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
CL from Chame Bay, 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1198,477,500]" name="Panama" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">Panama</collectingCountry>
, and the illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rios" box="[299,607,511,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" refString="Rios, R. &amp; Carvacho, A. (1983) Caridean shrimps of the Gulf of California III. Leptalpheus mexicanus, new species (Crustacea, Decapoda, Alpheidae). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 3, 306 - 313. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1548265" type="journal article" year="1983">
Ríos and Carvacho (
<number box="[537,598,512,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. He noted that the major cheliped of 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1197,512,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1197,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is stouter than in 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the anterior margin of the antennal scaphocerite of 
<taxonomicName box="[868,1017,548,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[868,1017,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less convex than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1429,549,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1280,1429,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the first carpal article of the second pereiopod is relatively longer in 
<taxonomicName box="[941,1090,584,608]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[941,1090,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that the two species also differ in the shape of the lateral tooth of the protopod (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rios" box="[795,1056,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" refString="Rios, R. &amp; Carvacho, A. (1983) Caridean shrimps of the Gulf of California III. Leptalpheus mexicanus, new species (Crustacea, Decapoda, Alpheidae). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 3, 306 - 313. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1548265" type="journal article" year="1983">
Ríos &amp; Carvacho 
<number box="[996,1056,620,644]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<number box="[1111,1122,620,644]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="1.0">1</number>
e and 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" box="[1192,1327,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" refString="Anker, A. (2011) Six new species and three new records of infaunal alpheid shrimps from the genera Leptalpheus Williams, 1965 and Fenneralpheus Felder &amp; Manning, 1986 (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zootaxa, 3041, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2011">
Anker 
<number box="[1268,1327,620,644]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<date box="[1382,1423,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="1915-01">
<number box="[1382,1412,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="15.0">15</number>
I
</date>
). We consider, however, that these characters are very relative and might reflect an intraspecic variation. We are reluctent to include 
<taxonomicName box="[374,521,692,716]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristatus">
<emphasis box="[374,521,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[752,899,693,716]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Leptalpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[752,899,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">L. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, as pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker" box="[1159,1313,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" refString="Anker, A. (2011) Six new species and three new records of infaunal alpheid shrimps from the genera Leptalpheus Williams, 1965 and Fenneralpheus Felder &amp; Manning, 1986 (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zootaxa, 3041, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2011">
Anker (
<number box="[1245,1305,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, additional material of both nominal species should be collected from the 
<typeStatus box="[871,919,728,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="581">type</typeStatus>
localities and within their distribution range, and carefully examined. Additionally, a molecular comparison would be highly desirable.
</paragraph>
